defmodule Solution do
  @spec count_stepping_numbers(low :: String.t(), high :: String.t()) :: integer()
  def count_stepping_numbers(low, high) do
    {low_num, high_num} = {String.to_integer(low), String.to_integer(high)}
    steps = for n <- 0..9, do: dfs(n, low_num, high_num, 0)
    Enum.sum(steps)
  end

  defp dfs(_current, _low, high, count) when _current > high, do: count

  defp dfs(current, low, high, count) when current >= low and current <= high do
    if current > 0 do
      count = count + 1
    end

    if current == 0 do
      Enum.reduce(1..9, count, fn x, acc -> dfs(x, low, high, acc) end)
    else
      last_digit = rem(current, 10)
      neighbors = []

      neighbors =
        if last_digit > 0, do: [current * 10 + last_digit - 1 | neighbors], else: neighbors

      neighbors =
        if last_digit < 9, do: [current * 10 + last_digit + 1 | neighbors], else: neighbors

      Enum.reduce(neighbors, count, fn x, acc -> dfs(x, low, high, acc) end)
    end
  end

  defp dfs(current, low, high, count) do
    if current == 0 do
      Enum.reduce(1..9, count, fn x, acc -> dfs(x, low, high, acc) end)
    else
      last_digit = rem(current, 10)
      neighbors = []

      neighbors =
        if last_digit > 0, do: [current * 10 + last_digit - 1 | neighbors], else: neighbors

      neighbors =
        if last_digit < 9, do: [current * 10 + last_digit + 1 | neighbors], else: neighbors

      Enum.reduce(neighbors, count, fn x, acc -> dfs(x, low, high, acc) end)
    end
  end
end
